The paper proposes an automatic approach for the classification of food-related environments in egocentric photo-streams. This involves computer vision techniques for scene classification (cs.CV), as well as human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects related to the use of wearable cameras. The paper also mentions the use of semantic hierarchies (cs.IR) and machine learning models (cs.LG) for the classification task.
